# Modal UX (Golden English)

## Objective

`<dialog>` surfaces (`Modal` from `@/components/atoms/Modal`) must clarify **keyboard focus**, **visible dismiss controls**, and **scroll ergonomics**. Very long transactional flows still belong on standalone routes‚Äînot endless modals.

## Backdrop treatment

`::backdrop` uses **blur + tint** (`backdrop-blur-md`, `backdrop-saturate`, `color-mix` tinted against app shells) distinguishing foreground vs background stacks.

Avoid flat monochrome overlays lacking blur unless justified via ADR or explicit design approval.

## Dismiss visibility

Dismissible dialogs must expose **`closeLabel`** (dictionary key such as `common.modalClose`, or coherent cancel wording) powering the explicit header close control (**icon + text**).

Avoid relying exclusively on footer buttons while the chrome could still show dismiss affordances.

## Sizing / responsive behavior

`Modal` enforces **`max-w-[calc(100vw-2rem)]`** (prevents bleed) layered with **`sm:max-w-lg md:max-w-xl lg:max-w-2xl`** so dialogs scale until hitting sensible ceilings‚Äî`dialogClassName` may override widths (for example **`max-w-4xl`** when necessary).

Bodies opt into **`@container`** grids so internals use **`@sm:`/`@md:`** tied to modal width‚Äînot only global breakpoints.

## Scrolling ergonomics

- When overflowing vertically, soften top/bottom scrims hinting unseen content (**gradients tinted with `--color-surface`**).
- Bodies leverage **`flex-1 min-h-0 overflow-y-auto`** targeting up to **`min(92dvh, calc(100dvh - 2rem))`**, avoiding artificial `48rem` caps chopping tall content prematurely.
- **Very long narratives** migrate to routed pages/detail panels (`?detail=`) instead of ‚Äúscroll skyscrapers‚Äù inside dialogs.
- **Nested lists/logs** inside modals may keep local **`max-height` + scrolling**‚Äîespecially deterministic bounded logs (`import traces`, etc.).

## Copy localization

Titles + **`closeLabel`** route through dictionaries (**`src/dictionaries/en.json` + `es.json`**, leaning on **`common.modalClose`** when reused).

## `Modal` QA checklist when editing

- [ ] `disableClose=false` ‚áí **`closeLabel` present**.
- [ ] Evaluate whether oversized flows warrant dedicated routes versus modal cramming.
- [ ] Visible copy dictionary-backed (**`09-i18n-copy.mdc`**)?
